    "scenario_findings": "Deterministic projections (T1) show the plan succeeding if returns are steady, but Monte Carlo stress tests (T2) reveal a critical weakness, with a 96% failure rate. This disparity is driven by the low expected return of the 401(k) Treasury allocation. Under stochastic market conditions, the current portfolio growth is insufficient to fund both college in 2040 and retirement in 2052.",
    "key_assumptions_and_uncertainties": "Analysis assumes Michael's annual bonus is consistently paid at target levels; without it, net savings are negligible. It assumes Emily's part-time income remains stable. College costs are estimated at $120k total, which may vary based on school choice. Inflation is assumed at 3%.",
